# .trivyignore — CVEs accepted as upstream-only or false positives.
#
# The CI Trivy step also uses ignore-unfixed: true, so only CVEs with
# available Debian patches will fail the build. This file catches fixed
# CVEs that are still acceptable (e.g. not exploitable in our context).
#
# Review this file when upgrading the base image (python:3.14-slim).
#
# Format:
#   # reason for ignoring
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN

# gh (Go stdlib) — bundled for CI convenience, not used at runtime.
# Fixed in gh 1.26.4; will clear on next base-image rebuild.
CVE-2026-42504
